The API acts as a bridge between applications and your custom ML model, accepting structured and cleaned tweet dataset (like text, timestamp, media, and brand) for prediction or generation tasks.
It processes these inputs, calling the model we built, and returns results (such as predicted likes or generated tweet text) in a column like csv or google spreadsheet
, along with clear error handling for reliability and easy integration.

